President Obama released a statement on the one year anniversary of the death of Polish President Lech Kaczynski and his delegation. He expressed his condolences and honored the memory of the 96 Polish patriots who tragically lost their lives. The President acknowledged the devastation caused by the wreckage in Smolensk and highlighted the unity and strength displayed by the Polish people during this difficult time. He emphasized the strong relationship between the United States and Poland and expressed his commitment to deepening these ties during his upcoming visit to Warsaw.